!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

incredulous /ɪnˈkrɛdjʊləs/

1. ADJ If someone is incredulous , they are unable to believe something because it is very surprising or shocking. 怀疑的 

例： 'He made you do it?' Her voice was incredulous. “他让你做的？”她的声音是怀疑的。 

2. incredulously ADV 怀疑地 [ADV with v] 

例： 'You told Pete?' Rachel said incredulously. 'I can't believe it!' “你告诉皮特了？”雷切尔怀疑地说道。“真不敢相信！”

</div>

